* [[Dad]] - [[Troll Stronghold]] 

==Strategy==
Run to any corner except the south-east corner, drink all your [[absorption]]s and sip a dose of [[Overload (Nightmare Zone)|overload]]. Feel the [[Locator orb]] or guzzle the [[dwarven rock cake]] down to 1 [[Hitpoints]]. Quickly turn on and off [[Rapid Heal]] to reset Hitpoints regeneration. Turn on [[Piety]] and attack or use auto-retaliate.

Drink [[prayer potion]]s as needed, flick Rapid Heal on and off once every 50-60 seconds to avoid regenerating to 2 Hitpoints. This maximises damage dealt and minimises absorption points used. If your Hitpoints goes above 1, feel the locator orb or guzzle the dwarven rock cake, if it is not working run away temporarily. As the overload expires, either run or turn on protection prayers temporarily to avoid wasting absorption points, drink another dose of overload and continue as before.

Experienced prayer flickers can set up quick-prayers to simultaneously activate Rapid Heal and their best offensive prayer. This improves damage output, stops accidental regeneration, and maximises Prayer points without using prayer potions, but this requires significantly more effort and attention.

Do '''not''' activate Ultimate Force. Activate Zapper and Recurrent Damage to increase points per hour, this may slightly affect experience gained only if you normally kill the bosses before new ones take their place. Activate Power Surge, switch equipment and use your special attack weapon, it lasts 45 seconds.

|-|
Melee (Absorption, AFK)=
Using normal customisable rumble with [[absorption]]s allows for 20 minutes of AFK melee training. After 20 minutes, the player will stop attacking and must manually start attacking again to reset the timer.

Players can gain up to 85,000â€“90,000 experience per hour, and sustain for 3â€“6 hours per session depending on equipment and stats. While this method does earn slightly more Nightmare Zone points than spent on absorptions, players looking to solely gain points are advised to use other setups.

It is possible to use this setup on customisable hard mode; however, bosses hit much harder in the hard mode, requiring more absorption potions. This does net more points (250k/hr+) and is a good mix of points and experience, especially for [[Ironmen]] looking to imbue items.

Players looking to gain more experience per hour are advised to use the Dharok's setup for much faster experience.

==Equipment==
The [[ghrazi rapier]], [[inquisitor's mace]], or [[Blade of saeldor (c)]] with [[Bandos armour]] offers the best experience per hour with good sustainability due to its high defences. [[Toktz-xil-ak]] along with full [[obsidian armour]] and [[berserker necklace]] offers the next best experience per hour and is a more affordable option, however it has much worse sustainability due to low defensive stats. Players who want sustainability but cannot afford a ghrazi rapier can use an [[abyssal whip]] (for training [[Attack]] or [[Defence]]) or [[abyssal bludgeon]] (for training [[Strength]]) along with Bandos armour.
