* [[Nazastarool]] ([[Shilo Village]]): Has multiple forms which reduces points per hour, although this does not affect experience rates.
* [[Black Knight Titan]] ([[Holy Grail]]): Deals high damage, which lowers sustainability.
* [[Bouncer]] ([[Fight Arena]]): Deals high damage, which lowers sustainability.

==Strategy==
Run to the middle of the arena. Use [[absorption]]s until 951-1000 absorption points, and optionally feel a [[locator orb]] or guzzle a [[dwarven rock cake]] down to 1 [[Hitpoints]] then sip a [[super combat potion]]. Repeat every 15â€“20 minutes.

Using a locator orb or a dwarven rock cake is optional but allows for longer sessions, minimising the amount of absorption points used to tank damage (especially using [[obsidian armour]]).
|-|
Ranged (Absorption, AFK)=
In order to maximise AFK duration, a customisable normal rumble with [[absorption]]s allows for 20 minutes of AFK ranged training, after which the player will stop attacking and must manually start attacking again to reset the timer. [[Experience]] rates are up to 155,000 per hour using a [[toxic blowpipe]] or 70,000 experience with a [[magic shortbow (i)]], sustainable for 3â€“6 hours per session depending on equipment and stats. While this method does earn slightly more Nightmare Zone points than spent on absorptions, players looking to gain points are advised to use other setups.

It is possible to use this setup on customisable hard mode, but only recommended if not being as AFK, bosses hit harder in hard mode so it is much more important to flick [[Rapid Heal]] and use a [[locator orb]] or [[dwarven rock cake]].

==Equipment==
[[Void Knight equipment]] offers the best experience per hour, however due to low defence bonuses it is recommended to use higher defence armour. [[Armadyl armour]] is the best replacement, followed by [[blessed dragonhide armour]] and normal [[dragonhide armour]]. It is recommended to wear a tank helmet, such as the [[justiciar faceguard]] for better defence as the slight accuracy loss has minimal effect on damage output. If even more [[defence bonus]] is needed, other Ranged equipment can be replaced with more defensive pieces, such as [[Bandos tassets]] or [[ring of suffering (i)]].

