AFK=
This method utilises disabling [[Dream Mentor]] and [[Desert Treasure]] bosses due to a mechanic, where if Dream Mentor is enabled but Desert Treasure is not, point rewards are reduced to one sixth of their original value.{{CiteReddit|author=Docter_Bogs|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/2007scape/comments/k6n3gg/i_figured_out_how_nightmare_zone_points_are/|title=I figured out how Nightmare Zone points are calculated...|quote=All your points are multiplied by 1/6 if (...) Dream Mentor bosses are turned ON and Desert Treasure bosses are turned OFF|date=4 December 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/wip/28fED|archivedate=11 January 2022}} To maximise AFK, disabling Desert Treasure and [[Recipe for Disaster]] bosses is preferable due to the bosses either being click-intensive or requiring attention, and disable [[Dream Mentor]] to avoid the point penalty.

==Gear==
The gear recommended for this method in order of best to worst is on other parts of the strategy page: [[#Melee|Dharok, Obsidian]], [[#Melee (Absorption, AFK)|highest strength gear]], [[#Melee (Prayer)|or mixed Strength bonus and Prayer gear]].

==Strategy==
Boost with an [[Overload (Nightmare Zone)|overload]], consume 1000 points of [[absorption]] points, and feel the [[Locator orb]] or guzzle the [[dwarven rock cake]] down to 1 [[Hitpoints]]. Quickly turn [[Rapid Heal]] on and off to reset Hitpoints regeneration and do so every 50-60 seconds to maintain 1 Hitpoints. Make sure [[Auto Retaliate]] is on.

Follow the boss kill priority list provided to maximise points gained.

'''Never''' use Ultimate Force power-up. Always use the Power Surge power-up and use the special attack weapon constantly. Use Recurrent Damage and Zapper whenever for higher points per hour.

==Bosses==
Make sure the following bosses are disabled:
* [[Recipe for Disaster]] and [[Desert Treasure]] bosses (due to non-AFK mechanics)
** [[Dream Mentor]] bosses (due to point penalty if Desert Treasure is off)
* [[Corrupt Lizardman]] (deals poison through absorption potions)
* [[Elvarg]] (drains stats and prayer points)
* [[Chronozon]] (requires casting 4 different magic spells)
* [[Dagannoth mother]] (requires actively switching attack style)
* [[Barrelchest]] (drains prayer)
* [[Glod]] (drains prayer)
* [[Witch's experiment]] (4-phase boss with low point reward)
* [[Nazastarool]] (3-phase boss)
* [[Slagilith]] (66% reduced damage for non-pickaxes)
* [[Tanglefoot]] (Requires secateurs to damage)

Optional disables that will make it more AFK, but less points per hour:
* [[Giant Roc]] (due to stun and knock back)
* [[Dad]] (due to stun and knock back)
* [[Essyllt]] (due to stat drain and a short stun)
* [[Treus Dayth]] (moves around after damage)

